<br>
Higher parry is great if you can keep the people beating on you in front of you. The damage you deal can be from any postion.<br>
<br>
If you want the higher parry even after all the discussion, I'd think about the 44slash/50DW/rest in parry spec. That way you at least have the best chance at your offhand swinging and max flurry damage. It also keeps you near the cap for weaponskill.<br>
