<br>
merc is my main toon since daoc came out and from what i remember most other mercs thought i was mad but hey , spec is a personal thing and i loved my original spec to the point of i'm now making a new merc from scratch , my original spec was ...errrmmm... 29 Sla - 50 DW - 49 Parry (eventually lowered parry to 39 and rest into Sla ) , i can hear the sharp intakes of breath and laughter already but think back to the days when Mythic still claimed there was NO <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8o --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/nerd.gif ALT="8o"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   RvR block/parry/evade bug , all you old hands know what i'm talking about and back then beeelieeeve me , that spec rocked , if it wasn't for the fact ( and i'm not gonna embarrass myself futher with details ) i'm on a damn slow comp atm for the most part it'd still rock <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  .<br>
<br>
 ok ,  even i can think of ways to improve it such as 44 Sla - DW 50 - Parry 39 blah blah in shield , then there's also... Dualist's Reflexes Passive N/A 1 3 6 10 14 Augmented Dexterity 2 Additional 3% dual wield chance/damage for dual wield/left axe users per level of this ability.....Aug St if a Sla merc will also help raise your Dam output ,  so in effect you could lower DW and keep Sla or Parry higher or vica versa , i will point out this though , when we still had caps dex had a higher top end so parry would actually return benifits from being higher spec'd and with the bug it worked great , erroll flynn never parried as much as i did <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   .<br>
<br>
style wise if your not looking to max both Sla - Dw then i'd recommend DW at least to 44 , reason : this gives you both Shadows Rain + Hypnotic Darkness which if you plan on being a style/positional fighter you'll need for the Reflections(parry)-Hypnotic Darkness(stunned) combo followed by the Flank - Shadows Rain combo wich is bleed and hinder i think but any way you cut it they're a lot of damage damn quickly .<br>
<br>
sla has a huge gap of nothing really between Amy Sla at 29 and Dia Sla at 50 , the fillers can be used from DW line usually with less End cost so to be honest i'd say aim for 29 then plow all spare points into Sla hopefully to at least 35 as that will mean at RR5 you'll still reach 50 Sla , by the time you start factoring in RA's , MoParry - Duelists Reflexes - Dodger - Aug St and so on alot will change.....<br>
<br>
as for Duel Shadows/Diamond Slash , Dia Sla is a nice high dam finish to a anytime combo while Duel Shadows is a front positional 20-30 bleed , basicaly an extr 25 dam on average if your toe to toe with your target , ( only a fool stays toe to toe with a merc in RvR these days , enter exceptions here ...  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   ) <br>
<br>
